Introduction

Heartcore was a South Korean co-ed hip-hop group formed under Hi-Lite Records in 2021, composed of Reddy, Swervy, Yosi and SUI.

They are presumed to have disbanded in 2022 when Hi-Lite Records went out of business. There has been no activity from the group since.
